The tarter sauce on the Crab Cakes was home made and was perfect, I could of licked that sauce bowl.
The "good gravy" was really f'ing good!
It wasn't a traditional brown gravy but more of a clear color.
I am a mashed potatoe whore so I know good potatoes and these were killer!
I didn't need to use any kind of sauce for my crab cakes or filet, they were good just the way they came, filled with flavor.
I also ordered a Long Island that was one of the best I've ever had, later the waiter told me the sweet and sour was home made too!
Being so impressed with everything, we decided to do two desserts.
We had the white chocolate brownie and the bread pudding.
Both rich and tasty.
The waiter warned me that  I might not be able to finish both desserts ( boy, he didn't know who he was talking to!
) I finished all my plates and dessert!
I was so incredibly happy with this place.
