A lazy Sunday afternoon, post-movie, early dinner.
It was Father's Day, and I guess we timed it just right.
We were immediately seated in the Bar area, which seemed a bit odd to me, but the table was nice, and I was there for the company, not the floor to ceiling multi-colored liquor display.
This place has a modern, upscale but casual feel.
The bar area is kinda tucked into a corner, and the seating is elevated over the dining area, so you do get a good overview of the dining room.
Our waittress was very knowledgeable and efficient, spending about 5 minutes reciting all the specials, soups, salads and FD deals.
I'm not sure I could memorize all that she spit out, it was impressive.
Shortly after seating us, the place filled to the brim, and apparently, when it's hot out, people get to stand around in the bar.
This kinda took a bit from the ambiance, I felt like I was eating and watching a crowd.
Tempted by the BBQ ribs, I decided to have a go at it.
This was a full rack of smokey-tender back ribs, that pretty much fell off the bone.
I cleaned all the bones, made a big pile of meat on my plate, poured some sauce over it and chowed down.
Oddly, they did not have cole slaw to go with this dish, so I had fries instead.
Overall, it was pretty darned good.
My youngest had a Caesar salad with chicken, she did not like the huge croutons - said they were too oily.
I tried one, and it was soaked in clarified butter - which pretty much tasted like a bon-bon to me.
I think you could soad a napkin in butter and I would scarf it.
A fresh Iced Tea to drink and efficient service rounded out the meal.

